obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (43585)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143&sectionId=43585&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Epidemic Diseases Act, 1897.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2***] ^3* * *`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.0. 1950.`
  line
  line `2. The words, figures and letters "except the territories which, immediately before the 1st November, 1956, were`
  line `comprised in Part B States" omitted by Act 34 of 2020, s. 2 (w.e.f. 22-4-2020).`
  line
  line `3. The word "and" rep. by Act 10 of 1914, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `4. Sub-section (3) rep. by s. 3 and the Second Schedule, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_a:
  sectionId (50452)
  sectionNo 1A
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 34 of 2020, s. 3 (w.e.f. 22-4-2020)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143&sectionId=50452&sectionno=1A&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143
obj_root_law_sections_1_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[1A. Definitions.--In this, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "act of violence" includes any of the following acts committed by any person against a`
  line `healthcare service personnel serving during an epidemic, which causes or may cause--`
  line
  line `(i) harassment impacting the living or working conditions of such healthcare service`
  line `personnel and preventing him from discharging his duties;`
  line
  line `(ii) harm, injury, hurt, intimidation or danger to the life of such healthcare service`
  line `personnel, either within the premises of a clinical establishment or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(iii) obstruction or hindrance to such healthcare service personnel in the discharge of`
  line `his duties, either within the premises of a clinical establishment or otherwise; or`
  line
  line `(iv) loss or damage to any property or documents in the custody of, or in relation to,`
  line `such healthcare service personnel;`
  line
  line `(b) "healthcare service personnel" means a person who while carrying out his duties in`
  line `relation to epidemic related responsibilities, may come in direct contact with affected patients`
  line `and thereby is at the risk of being impacted by such disease, and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) any public and clinical healthcare provider such as doctor, nurse, paramedical`
  line `worker and community health worker;`
  line
  line `(ii) any other person empowered under the Act to take measures to prevent the`
  line `outbreak of the disease or spread thereof; and`
  line
  line `(iii) any person declared as such by the State Government, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(c) "property" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a clinical establishment as defined in the Clinical Establishments (Registration and`
  line `Regulation) Act, 2010 (23 of 2010);`
  line
  line `(ii) any facility identified for quarantine and isolation of patients during an epidemic;`
  line
  line `(iii) a mobile medical unit; and`
  line
  line `(iv) any other property in which a healthcare service personnel has direct interest in`
  line `relating to the epidemic;`
  line
  line `(d) the words and expressions used herein and not defined, but defined in the Indian Ports`
  line `Act, 1908 (15 of 1908), the Aircraft Act, 1934 (22 of 1934) or the Land Ports Authority of`
  line `India Act, 2010 (31 of 2010), as the case may be, shall have the same meaning as assign ed to`
  line `them in that Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (43586)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to take special measures and prescribe regulations as to dangerous epidemic disease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143&sectionId=43586&sectionno=2&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^12. Power to take special measures and prescribe regulations as to dangerous epidemic`
  line `disease.--(1) When at any time the ^2[State Government] is satisfied that ^2[the State] or any part`
  line `thereof is visited by, or threatened with, an outbreak of any dangerous epidemic disease, the ^3[State`
  line `Government], if ^4[it] thinks that the ordinary provisions of the law for the time being in force are`
  line `insufficient for the purpose, may take, or require or empower any person to take, such me asures`
  line `and, by public notice, prescribe such temporary regulations to be observed by the public or by any`
  line `person or class of persons as ^4[it] shall deem necessary to prevent the outbreak of such disease or`
  line `the spread thereof, and may determine in what manner and by whom any expenses incurred`
  line `(including compensation if any) shall be defrayed.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, the ^2[State`
  line `Government] may take measures and prescribe regulations for--`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) the inspection of persons travelling by railway or otherwise, and the segregation, in hospital,`
  line `temporary accommodation or otherwise, of persons suspected by the inspecting officer of being infected`
  line `with any such disease.`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. For Notifications issued under this section, see different local Rules and Orders.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "G.G. in C."`
  line
  line `3. Subs., ibid., for "India".`
  line
  line `4. Subs., ibid., for "he".`
  line
  line `5. Paragraph (a) omitted, ibid.`
  line
  line `6. Sub-section (3) omitted by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a:
  sectionId (43587)
  sectionNo 2A
  orderNo 4
  title `Powers of Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143&sectionId=43587&sectionno=2A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 [2A. Powers of Central Government.--When the Central Government is satisfied that India`
  line `or any part thereof is visited by, or threatened with, an outbreak of any dangerous epidemic`
  line `disease and that the ordinary provisions of the law for the time being in force are insuffici ent to`
  line `prevent the outbreak of such disease or the spread thereof, the Central Government may take`
  line `measures and prescribe regulations for the inspection of any ship or vessel leaving or arriving at`
  line `any port in ^2[the territories to which this Act extends] and for such detention thereof, or of any`
  line `person intending to sail therein, or arriving thereby, as may be necessary.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2 and the First Schedule. Earlier substituted by the A.O.1937.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No.2) Order, 1956, for "a Part A State or a Part C State".`
obj_root_law_sections_2_b:
  sectionId (50453)
  sectionNo 2B
  orderNo 5
  title `Prohibition of violence against healthcare service personnel and damage to property`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 34 of 2020, s. 5 (w.e.f. 22-4-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143&sectionId=50453&sectionno=2B&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143
obj_root_law_sections_2_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[2B. Prohibition of violence against healthcare service personnel and damage to property.--No`
  line `person shall indulge in any act of violence against a healthcare service personnel or cause any damage or`
  line `loss to any property during an epidemic.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (43588)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 6
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143&sectionId=43588&sectionno=3&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Any person disobeying any regulation or order made under this Act shall`
  line `be deemed to have committed an offence punishable under section 188 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Whoever,--`
  line
  line `(i) commits or abets the commission of an act of violence against a healthcare service`
  line `personnel; or`
  line
  line `(ii) abets or cause damage or loss to any property,`
  line
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three months, but`
  line `which may extend to five years, and with fine, which shall not be less than fifty thousand`
  line `rupees, but which may extend to two lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever, while committing an act of violence against a healthcare service personnel,`
  line `causes grievous hurt as defined in section 320 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) to such`
  line `person, shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six`
  line `months, but which may extend to seven years and with fine, which shall not be less than one`
  line `lakh rupees, but which may extend to five lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 3 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 34 of 2020, s. 6 (w.e.f. 22-4-2020).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 34 of 2020, s. 6 (w.e.f. 22-4-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (50454)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 7
  title `Cognizance, investigation and trial of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-4-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143&sectionId=50454&sectionno=3A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[3A. Cognizance, investigation and trial of offences.--Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),--`
  line
  line `(i) an offence punishable under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of section 3 shall be`
  line `cognizable and non-bailable;`
  line
  line `(ii) any case registered under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of section 3 shall be`
  line `investigated by a police officer not below the rank of Inspector;`
  line
  line `(iii) investigation of a case under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of section 3 shall`
  line `be completed within a period of thirty days from the date of registration of the First`
  line `Information Report;`
  line
  line `(iv) in every inquiry or trial of a case under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 3, the proceedings shall be held as expeditiously as possible, and in particular,`
  line `when the examination of witnesses has once begun, the same shall be continued from day`
  line `to day until all the witnessed in attendance have been examined, unless the Court finds the`
  line `adjournment of the same beyond the following day to be necessary for reasons to be`
  line `recorded, and an endeavor shall be made to ensure that the inquiry or trial is concluded`
  line `within a period of one year:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the trial is not concluded within the said period, the Judge shall`
  line `record the reasons for not having done so:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the said period may be extended by such further period, for reasons`
  line `to be recorded in writing, but not exceeding six months at a time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_b:
  sectionId (50455)
  sectionNo 3B
  orderNo 8
  title `Composition of certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-4-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143&sectionId=50455&sectionno=3B&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143
obj_root_law_sections_3_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[3B. Composition of certain offences.--Where a person is prosecuted for committing an`
  line `offence punishable under sub-section (2) of section 3, such offence may, with the permission`
  line `of the Court, be compounded by the person against whom such act of violence is committed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_c:
  sectionId (50456)
  sectionNo 3C
  orderNo 9
  title `Presumption as to certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-4-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143&sectionId=50456&sectionno=3C&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143
obj_root_law_sections_3_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[3C. Presumption as to certain offences.--Where a person is prosecuted for committing`
  line `an offence punishable under sub-section (3) of section 3, the Court shall presume that such`
  line `person has committed such offence, unless the contrary is proved.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_d:
  sectionId (50457)
  sectionNo 3D
  orderNo 10
  title `Presumption of culpable mental state.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-4-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143&sectionId=50457&sectionno=3D&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143
obj_root_law_sections_3_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[3D. Presumption of culpable mental state.--(1) In any prosecution for an offence under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 3 which requires a culpable mental state on the part of the accused,`
  line `the Court shall presume the existence of such mental state, but it shall be a defence for the`
  line `accused to prove the fact that he had no such mental state with respect to the act charged as an`
  line `offence in that prosecution.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, a fact is said to be proved only when the Court`
  line `believes it to exist beyond reasonable doubt and not merely when its existenc e is established`
  line `by a preponderance of probability.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, "culpable mental state" includes intention, motive,`
  line `knowledge of a fact and the belief in, or reason to believe, a fact.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_e:
  sectionId (50458)
  sectionNo 3E
  orderNo 11
  title `Compensation for acts of violence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-4-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143&sectionId=50458&sectionno=3E&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143
obj_root_law_sections_3_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[3E. Compensation for acts of violence.--(1) In addition to the punishment provided for`
  line `an offence under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of section 3, the person so convicted shall`
  line `also be liable to pay, by way of compensation, such amount, as may be determined by the`
  line `Court for causing hurt or grievous hurt to any healthcare service personnel.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the composition of an offence under section 3B, in case of damage to`
  line `any property or loss caused, the compensation payable shall be twice the amount of fair`
  line `market value of the damaged property or the loss caused, as may be determined by the Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon failure to pay the compensation awarded under sub-sections (1) and (2), such`
  line `amount shall be recovered as an arrear of land revenue under the Revenue Recovery Act, 1890`
  line `(1 of 1890).]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (43589)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 12
  title `Protection to persons acting under Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143&sectionId=43589&sectionno=4&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_189703_1523337650143
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against any person for anything done or in good faith intended to be done under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
